{
  "stem": "2723.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "There-- there was terrific lot of screaming, and quarreling, and bickering, and nastiness out of pure, sheer despair.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "This man was wonderful.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "He kept telling us to lean on him and to think that we'd-- with our parents.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "He abused the privilege with me, and I was grown up overnight.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "He became very tactile during the night, and tried very hard to do something to me that I didn't understand.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And I got very frightened.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "My sister was asleep, and I broke free.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "There was nowhere to really go, but I wound my way through the wagon to the chagrin and anger and-- and fury of those that were there, and sat in a corner, separately.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "I'm telling you this because it's very important to what happened later.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "When daybreak came, my sister realized I wasn't there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And she called me back and I wouldn't come.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And she got very, very angry with me, and she said, 'You always had to be different.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "You always were trying to be different from me.' And so it went, like sisters do.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And I just couldn't go back.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "I had an ally in the perpetrator because he said to my sister, 'Oh, let her be.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "She-- she just wants to be away from us for a while.' And so we actually arrived in what turned out to be Auschwitz at separate ends of the wagon.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Took forever 'til the doors were opened.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "By then, the stench and the dreadful characteristics of tested human beings were at the fore, and we were really aware of the fact that we were quite ready to claw at each other.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "When the doors were broken open, the first call was 'men out,' so the man was gone.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
